sentences: Julian Lage ( LAHZH; born December 25, 1987) is an American guitarist and composer.
A child prodigy, Lage was the subject of the 1996 short documentary film Jules at Eight.
At 12, he performed at the 2000 Grammy Awards.
Three years later, he became a faculty member of the Stanford Jazz Workshop at Stanford University.
He graduated from the Berklee College of Music in 2008.
For the 2017 guitar duo album Mount Royal, Lage and Eldridge received a Grammy nomination for Best Contemporary Instrumental Album.
